sentences: Countess Stephanie von Wurmbrand-Stuppach (December 26, 1849 â€“ February 16, 1919) was a Hungarian pianist and composer.
Stephanie von Wurmbrand-Stuppach was born in Pressburg (now Bratislava), Hungary.
She gave concerts in Vienna and other major cities in Europe.
On July 6, 1869, she married Count Ernst von Wurmbrand-Stuppach, brother of Adelma Vay.
In recognition of her achievements she received a Silver Medal for Art and Science from Ernest II, Duke of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha.
